  "texts": [
    "Visual attention helps concentrate attention on the key areas of the human body, enabling more accurate regression of the keypoints.",
    "Common visual attention mechanisms [43] [44] [45] [46], such as channel attention and spatial attention, typically model feature information from either channel or spatial dimensions.",
    "Channel attention 43, 44 assigns weights to different feature channels and allocates adaptive weights to each channel.",
    "However, it models spatial information poorly and lacks sensitivity to the positions of the human keypoints.",
    "On the other hand, spatial attention 45, 46 helps improve the regression of spatial information related to human pose."
  ],
